    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-25T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-25T23:00:00-05:00" n="403"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d403">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/7487: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-26T11:00:00+07:00"
                            >May 26, 1942—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 3:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>605. For Secretary of the Treasury from Fox.</p>
                <p>“TF–40. 1. Arrived Chungking May 25.</p>
                <p>2. First impression is that economic situation gravely deteriorated in the last 4
                    months. Shall report at length in near future.<note n="70" xml:id="d403fn70">For
                        draft of Mr. Fox’s report, submitted by Mr. Adler after the death of Mr.
                        Fox, see telegram No. 841, July 15, from Ambassador Gauss, <ref
                            target="#pg_530">p. 530</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>3. In brief conference this morning Doctor Kung informed he had certain problems
                    involving Treasury he would take up with me at early opportunity.</p>
                <p>4. Have learned Hsi Te-mou<note n="71" xml:id="d403fn71">Representative of
                        Chinese Ministry of Finance and the Central Bank of China, designated for a
                        mission to the United States.</note> leaving for Washington at the end of
                    this week. He informed me Doctor Kung is sending him to take up certain matters
                    with T. V. Soong but according to other sources he is going to represent Central
                    Bank.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
